  "prompt": "Why there is no true love in this world?",
  "response": "Love exists in many forms, but it can be complex and challenging. While it's not accurate to say there's \"no true love,\" people may feel this way due to:\n\n1. Personal experiences\n- Past heartbreaks\n- Betrayals\n- Disappointments in relationships\n\n2. Societal influences\n- Media portrayal of relationships\n- High divorce rates\n- Changing relationship dynamics\n\n3. Individual perspectives\n- Unrealistic expectations\n- Trust issues\n- Fear of vulnerability\n\n4. Different love definitions\n- People understand love differently\n- Cultural variations\n- Personal interpretations\n\nHowever, true love does exist:\n- Between parents and children\n- In deep friendships\n- In committed romantic relationships\n- In selfless acts of care\n\nWays to experience true love:\n- Be vulnerable\n- Communicate openly\n- Practice empathy\n- Build trust\n- Accept imperfections\n- Work on self-love\n\nLove requires effort, understanding, and commitment. While challenging, genuine love is possible when both people are willing to invest emotionally and work together.\n\nRemember, love is a journey, not a destination. Your perspective and experiences shape your understanding of love.\n\nWould you like to discuss this further?",
